      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cli): add runtime capability discovery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- remove the redundant `gog agent` command namespace and dead command/test/docs paths\n- keep stable exit-code discovery at top-level `gog exit-codes`\n- add top-level `gog capabilities` for output, auth-method, safety-profile, command-guard, schema, exit-code, and MCP discovery\n- add a zero-argument `gog_capabilities` MCP tool that reports only redacted server-controlled safety/tool metadata\n- update bundled safe profiles so `capabilities`, `schema`, and `exit-codes` remain available\n\nThis replaces the design closed in #750. Automation contracts apply to the CLI as a whole, not a special agent mode.\n\nCloses #677.\n\n## Security\n\n- default CLI capability output does not open the keyring or disclose account identity, credential type, scopes, services, or token expiry\n- local credential inspection requires explicit `--include-auth`; identity requires separate `--include-account`\n- MCP accepts no disclosure arguments, never inspects credentials, and reflects enforced `--no-input` and untrusted-content wrapping\n- no tokens, secrets, key material, or keyring passwords are returned\n\n## Verification\n\n- `make ci`\n- structured autoreview: clean after fixing MCP effective safety-state reporting and bundled profile coverage\n- built binary smoke: top-level capabilities JSON/plain, exit-code JSON, removed `gog agent` parse path, MCP tool listing\n- sequential safe-binary builds: `agent-safe` and `readonly` both expose `capabilities` and report the correct baked profile\n- real clawdbot keyring/token path attempted; current local environment has no non-interactive keyring password and reports the stored clawdbot token invalid, so no auth state was changed\n",
        "branch": "feat/cli-capabilities-677",
